###  https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#Iberian_Margin
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#Iberian_Margin> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                              <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#RegionalFacility> ;
                                                     <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#RegionalFacility_is_part_of_a_RI> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#EMSO-PT> ;
                                                     <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#containsSite> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#IbMa-CSV> ,
                                                                                                        <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#IbMa-N> ;
                                                     <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#hasERICMembership> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#Iberian_Margin_EMSO_membership> ;
                                                     <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#hasRegionalTeamLeader> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#Carlos_SOUSA> ;
                                                     <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#isLedByOrganization> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#IPMA> ;
                                                     <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#dateFirstDeployment> "2021-05-01"^^xsd:date ;
                                                     <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#distanceFromLand> 11 ;
                                                     <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#maxWaterDepth> 1200 ;
                                                     <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "A região do Golfo de Cádis é extremamente importante para os riscos geológicos. Foi o local do devastador terramoto e tsunami de 1755 que afetou a Europa. A convergência das placas tectónicas africana e euroasiática torna esta região altamente ativa do ponto de vista sísmico e vulcânico. A Margem Ibérica é também uma região oceanográfica fundamental onde ocorre a troca de águas atlânticas e mediterrânicas, influenciando a circulação meridional do Atlântico (AMOC). Representa a parte mais setentrional do Sistema de Afloramento das Canárias (CCUS), caracterizado por forte afloramento costeiro e intensa dinâmica de mesoescala. Estas condições geológicas e oceanográficas favorecem ecossistemas bentónicos altamente diversos e desempenham um papel importante na distribuição de mamíferos marinhos e espécies de peixes."@pt ,
                                                                                            "La région du golfe de Cadix est particulièrement importante pour les aléas géologiques. Elle a été le siège du séisme et du tsunami dévastateurs de 1755 ayant affecté l’Europe. La convergence des plaques tectoniques africaine et eurasienne rend cette région fortement active sur les plans sismique et volcanique. La marge ibérique constitue également une zone océanographique clé où les eaux atlantiques et méditerranéennes s’échangent, influençant la circulation méridienne de retournement atlantique (AMOC). Elle représente la partie la plus septentrionale du système d’upwelling des Canaries (CCUS), caractérisé par des remontées d’eaux profondes et une forte dynamique méso-échelle. Ces conditions géologiques et océanographiques favorisent une grande diversité des communautés benthiques ainsi qu’un rôle majeur dans la répartition de nombreuses espèces de mammifères marins et de poissons."@fr ,
                                                                                            "The Gulf of Cadiz area is highly important for geo-hazards. It was the location of the devastating 1755 earthquake and tsunami that affected Europe. The convergence of the African and Eurasian tectonic plates makes this region seismically and volcanically active. The Iberian Margin is also a key oceanographic region where Atlantic and Mediterranean waters exchange, influencing the Atlantic Meridional Overturning Circulation (AMOC). It is the northernmost part of the Canary Current Upwelling System (CCUS), characterised by strong upwelling and mesoscale ocean dynamics. These geological and oceanographic conditions support highly diverse benthic ecosystems and play an important role in the distribution of marine mammals and fish species."@en ;
                                                     <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gulf_of_Cadiz> ,
                                                                                        <http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iberian_Peninsula> ,
                                                                                        <http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Atlantic_Ocean> ;
                                                     <http://schema.org/url> <https://emso-pt.pt/> ,
                                                                             <https://emso.eu/observatories-node/iberian-margin/> ;
                                                     rdfs:label "Iberian Margin"@el ,
                                                                "Iberian Margin"@en ,
                                                                "Iberian Margin"@es ,
                                                                "Iberian Margin"@fr ,
                                                                "Iberian Margin"@it ,
                                                                "Iberian Margin"@no ,
                                                                "Iberian Margin"@pt ,
                                                                "Iberian Margin"@ro ;
                                                     rdfs:seeAlso <https://emso-pt.pt/> ,
                                                                  <https://emso.eu/observatories-node/iberian-margin/> ;
                                                     <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "EMSO-PT Iberian Margin Regional Facility"@en ,
                                                                                                    "Infraestrutura regional EMSO-PT da Margem Ibérica"@pt ,
                                                                                                    "Infrastructure régionale EMSO-PT de la marge ibérique"@fr ;
                                                     <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "EMSO Regional Facility located on the Iberian Margin and operated within EMSO-PT for multidisciplinary ocean observation and geo-hazard monitoring activities."@en ,
                                                                                                      "Infraestrutura regional do EMSO localizada na Margem Ibérica e operada no âmbito do EMSO-PT para atividades multidisciplinares de observação oceânica e monitorização de riscos geológicos."@pt ,
                                                                                                      "Infrastructure régionale EMSO située sur la marge ibérique et exploitée dans le cadre d’EMSO-PT pour des activités multidisciplinaires d’observation océanique et de surveillance des aléas géologiques."@fr ;
                                                     <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#note> "IbMa"@en ;
                                                     <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Iberian Margin"@el ,
                                                                                                     "Iberian Margin"@en ,
                                                                                                     "Iberian Margin"@es ,
                                                                                                     "Iberian Margin"@fr ,
                                                                                                     "Iberian Margin"@it ,
                                                                                                     "Iberian Margin"@no ,
                                                                                                     "Iberian Margin"@pt ,
                                                                                                     "Iberian Margin"@ro .


