###  https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#MARMOR
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#MARMOR> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                      <http://schema.org/Project> ,
                                                      <https://w3id.org/cerif/vocab/Project> ,
                                                      <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#FundedProject> ;
                                             <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/depiction> <https://raw.githubusercontent.com/emso-eric/oso-ontology/main/images/marmor.png> ;
                                             <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#hasCountry> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#France> ;
                                             <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#hasLocation> <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#Mayotte> ;
                                             <https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#hasLogo> <https://raw.githubusercontent.com/emso-eric/oso-ontology/main/images/marmor.png> ;
                                             <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> """MARMOR (Marine Advanced Geophysical Research Equipment and Mayotte Multidisciplinary Observatory for Research and Response) est un projet d’une durée de huit ans financé par l’ANR.

Le projet MARMOR a un double objectif :

structurer la communauté scientifique française en fournissant à l’infrastructure de recherche Epos-France (anciennement Résif) les équipements nécessaires pour conduire des recherches d’excellence utilisant les outils de la sismologie et de la géodésie sous-marines,

mettre en place une infrastructure d’observation sous-marine à Mayotte afin d’assurer une surveillance sismologique continue, en temps réel et 24/7, et de conduire des recherches multidisciplinaires sur les phénomènes associés à la crise sismo-volcanique en cours."""@fr ,
                                                                                    """MARMOR (Marine Advanced Geophysical Research Equipment and Mayotte Multidisciplinary Observatory for Research and Response) is an eight-year project funded by the ANR.

The MARMOR project has two objectives:

to structure the French scientific community by providing the Epos-France research infrastructure (formerly Résif) with the equipment required to conduct high-level research using submarine seismology and geodesy tools,

to establish an underwater observation infrastructure in Mayotte in order to ensure continuous, real-time, 24/7 seismological monitoring and to support multidisciplinary research on the phenomena associated with the ongoing seismo-volcanic crisis."""@en ;
                                             <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Marine Advanced Geophysical Research Equipment and Mayotte Multidisciplinary Observatory for Research and Response (MARMOR)"@en ,
                                                                              "Marine Advanced Geophysical Research Equipment and Mayotte Multidisciplinary Observatory for Research and Response (MARMOR)"@fr ;
                                             <http://schema.org/logo> <https://raw.githubusercontent.com/emso-eric/oso-ontology/main/images/marmor.png> ;
                                             <http://schema.org/url> <https://www.marmor-project.org/fr> ;
                                             rdfs:label "MARMOR"@el ,
                                                        "MARMOR"@en ,
                                                        "MARMOR"@es ,
                                                        "MARMOR"@fr ,
                                                        "MARMOR"@it ,
                                                        "MARMOR"@no ,
                                                        "MARMOR"@pt ,
                                                        "MARMOR"@ro ;
                                             <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Marine Advanced Geophysical Research Equipment and Mayotte Multidisciplinary Observatory for Research and Response"@en ;
                                             <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Eight-year ANR-funded project developing advanced marine geophysical instrumentation and a multidisciplinary underwater observatory for long-term monitoring of the Mayotte seismo-volcanic crisis."@en ,
                                                                                              "Projet ANR d’une durée de huit ans visant à développer des équipements géophysiques marins avancés et un observatoire sous-marin multidisciplinaire pour le suivi à long terme de la crise sismo-volcanique de Mayotte."@fr ;
                                             <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "MARMOR"@el ,
                                                                                             "MARMOR"@en ,
                                                                                             "MARMOR"@es ,
                                                                                             "MARMOR"@fr ,
                                                                                             "MARMOR"@it ,
                                                                                             "MARMOR"@no ,
                                                                                             "MARMOR"@pt ,
                                                                                             "MARMOR"@ro .


